accepted_missions.description: A series of temporal anomalies have altered the universe, merging past, present, future, and mirror timelines into one. Work with Q to investigate these anomalies, and learn how you can bring order to this chaos.
Pirates, rogue holograms, and formerly eradicated diseases are only a few of the problems plaguing this area. Handle each in turn to bring order to the region.

From renegade androids to ancient civilizations born anew, the temporal crisis has brought chaos to every corner of the galaxy. Set the standard for all Starfleet captains by dealing with each threat in turn.
Q hasn't taken an active role in resolving the temporal anomaly crisis, and Starfleet is ready for answers. Get Q's attention, and then begin an epic journey into the Continuum itself.
Could the Federation be responsible for the temporal crisis? Captain Janeway can't confirm or deny she knows the answer, but she has sent Voyager's EMH to help investigate.
Q has volunteered to assist the Federation during this temporal crisis, but can he be trusted? Join legendary Starfleet captains of the past to seek help from other powerful beings.

The temporal crisis has brought new conflict to the already fractious Klingon Empire, where vengeance, deceit, and rebellion are the least of a captain's worries. Respond to these distress calls before the Empire falls further into disorder.
Aid the crew of the Discovery in matters both personal and professional, close to home and light years away.

crew.name: Revolutionary Damar
crew.flavor: Leader of the Cardassian revolution against the Dominion, Damar was killed by Jem'hadar shortly before the final assault.

action.name: What Small, Frail Creatures You Are

crew.name: Mirror Spock
crew.flavor: First Officer of the I.S.S Enterprise, Spock was a ruthless officer in the mirror universe's Terran Empire.

action.name: My People Will Find Your Ship

crew.name: Abraham Lincoln
crew.flavor: A simulacrum of the late President, created by the Excalbians to examine the difference between good and evil.

action.name: Let's See If You Can Beat That
I Can Take Care Of Myself

crew.name: Humanoid Figure
crew.flavor: Unable to appear physically, the elusive humanoid figure attempts to manipulate affairs from the distant 28th century.

action.name: There Won't Be A Next Time
How Are The Stone Knives And Bearskins?

crew.name: Armed Philippa Georgiou
crew.flavor: Captain Georgiou to excavate a Crepusculan well that had gone dry and save the species from drought.

crew.name: T'Mir
crew.flavor: Part of a Vulcan science vessel that crashed on Earth, T'Mir assumed command of the survivors.

crew.name: Nanoprobe Phlox
crew.flavor: After being infected with Borgs Nanoprobes, Phlox needs to think more like an Engineer than a Doctor to cure his condition.

crew.name: EV Suit Spock
crew.flavor: Feeling a connection to the consciousness of V-ger, Spock stole equipment to seek his answers.

action.name: It Was Better When We Were Separate

crew.name: Dominion Dukat
crew.flavor: As leader of Cardassia, Dukat delivered on his promise to retake Deep Space Nine from the Federation.

crew.name: T'Pring
crew.flavor: Not quite Spock's wife and not quite his betrothed, T'Pring claimed kal-if-fee in order to be with Stonn instead.

action.name: Let Us See What The Future Holds

crew.name: Ardra
crew.flavor: A legendary devil-figure on Ventax II, a con artist impersonated her in order to take control of the planet.

crew.name: Anastasia Komananov
crew.flavor: After a transporter accident, Kira's image is used by a holosuite program to display a Soviet secret agent.

crew.name: Courier Burnham
crew.flavor: Joining up with Booker, Burnham helps as a courier while she awaits the return of Discovery.

action.name: It Ain't Over Til It's Over
I Saw Hope In The Stars

crew.name: C.O.P. Founder Picard
crew.flavor: Stepping in for the missing Jonathan Archer, Picard helped form the Coalition of Planets. (Second Battle of New York player vote winner!)

action.name: Not a Conversation Killer at All

crew.name: Kurak
crew.flavor: An expert in warp field theory, Kurak attended Doctor Reyga's metaphasic shield test aboard the Enterprise-D.

crew.name: Judge Q
crew.flavor: All-powerful judge and jury, Q placed the Enterprise-D's crew on trial at Farpoint.

crew.name: Luau Paris
crew.flavor: Paris slips into his classic Big Daddy-O Surf Special shirt before attending a luau with his crewmates.

action.name: I Die Not For Myself But For You
I Didn't Want to Disillusion Him
You Know How Much I Hate To Lose

crew.name: Captain Klaa
crew.flavor: Eager to gain fame by defeating Kirk, Captain Klaa engaged the Enterprise-A at Nimbus III.

crew.name: First Goran'Agar
crew.flavor: Survivor of a crash landing, Goran'Agar was found to naturally produce the drug ketracel-white.

crew.name: Young Khan
crew.flavor: Ruler of a quarter of humanity during the Eugenics Wars, Khan escaped earth on the S.S. Botany Bay.

crew.name: Adira Tal
crew.flavor: Adira, now properly joined with the Trill Symbiont Tal, re-acquires their memories from their previous lives.

crew.name: Lothario Q
crew.flavor: Of all the females, of all the species, in all the galaxy--Q drops in to inform Janeway of his plans of becoming a parent.

action.name: The Old Michael Burnham is Dead

crew.name: Bridal Deanna Troi
crew.flavor: Celebrating their marriage, Deanna enjoys the festivities of her human heritage with a traditional reception.

crew.name: Soren
crew.flavor: A member of the androgynous J'naii species who later reveals she identifies as female--is joined by Riker on a rescue mission.

action.name: Logic Is The Beginning Of Wisdom

crew.name: Temporal Agent Seven
crew.flavor: A crew member on the timeship Relativity, she was later replaced by Seven of Nine.

crew.name: Mirror Doctor Culber
crew.flavor: A high-ranking physician in the Terran Empire who supported Lorca and Burnham's attempt to usurp the throne.

crew.name: Princess Jadzia
crew.flavor: In an attempt to entertain Major Kira, Jadzia arranged a visit to a Camelot holoprogram.

crew.name: Gary Seven
crew.flavor: A Class 1 Supervisor, Gary Seven spent his life on an alien world training for the day he would return to save Earth.

crew.name: Klingon Bride Jadzia
crew.flavor: Jadzia chose traditional Klingon wedding attire for her marriage to Lieutenant Commander Worf.

crew.name: Commander Kira Nerys
crew.flavor: To facilitate contact with the Cardassian rebels, Kira was given a Starfleet field commission.

crew.name: Mirror Tucker
crew.flavor: Chief Engineer of the I.S.S Enterprise, Tucker was able to prevent the U.S.S. Defiant from being lost to sabotage.

action.name: Do You Know Who I Am?

crew.name: Barry Waddle
crew.flavor: A Klingon Intelligence Operative disguised as a Human merchant, Barry was trapped on Cardassia Prime during the Klingon-Cardassian War.

crew.name: Changeling Founder
crew.flavor: One of many Founders, this changeling commanded all Dominion activity in the Alpha Quadrant.

crew.name: Klingon West
crew.flavor: In an attempt to assassinate the Federation President, Colonel West dons the disguise of a Klingon.

crew.name: Resistance Shakaar
crew.flavor: A part of the resistance during the Cardassian Occupation, Shakaar was later First Minister of Bajor.

action.name: Plans To The McKinley Rocket Base
For A Moment I Was Everywhere

crew.name: Carl, Guardian of Forever
crew.flavor: Carl, a new visual representation of the Guardian, stands guard over a trans-dimensional door in the thirty-second Century.

action.name: There's More Than One Way to Die.

crew.name: GI Chakotay
crew.flavor: While Voyager was under the control of the Hirogen, Chakotay was made to play the role of an Army captain.

crew.name: Warship Yar
crew.flavor: Refugee of an alternate universe in which the Enterprise-C fought daily battles against the Klingon Empire.

crew.name: KDF Gowron
crew.flavor: Gowron, son of M'Rel, was one of the final two challengers to succeed K'Mpec as the Klingon Chancellor.

crew.name: Tribble Quark
crew.flavor: Quark must deal with an infestation of Tribbles in his bar.

action.name: I'm Not Staying To Make Friends

crew.name: Luma Rahl Kira
crew.flavor: Kira travels back in time and poses as a comfort woman to learn the truth about her mother’s final years.

crew.name: Captain Picard Day Picard
crew.flavor: For a school holiday to celebrate the ship’s captain, a reluctant Picard must pick winners from students’ art projects.

crew.name: Desert Ben Sisko
crew.flavor: “Guided by a vision from the prophets, Sisko scours Tyree for the Orb of the Emissary."

action.name: I Know It’s Out There Someplace

crew.name: Desert Jake Sisko
crew.flavor: “Jake struggles to keep up with his father’s erratic search while tending to his exhausted grandfather.”

action.name: We've Got To Get Out Of Here

crew.name: Forra Gegen
crew.flavor: A Voth molecular paleontologist, Gegen learned that the saurian species had originally developed on Earth.

action.name: I'll See You In Hell First!

crew.name: Little Boy Blue Wesley
crew.flavor: A period-dressed holoprogram of Wesley Crusher enjoying a picnic with his mother before a fight breaks out.

action.name: I Thought We Had An Agreement
The Light, It Is Almost Like Music

crew.name: Balok
crew.flavor: Captain of the Fesarius, Balok manned his advanced ship alone. He used a puppet to intimidate and deceive potential threats due to his diminutive appearance.

action.name: It's about time you came back

crew.name: Klingon K'Ehleyr
crew.flavor: About to embark on a mission to re-integrate Klingons from a time of war, K'Ehleyr professes her feelings for Worf.

crew.name: Captain Morgan Bateson
crew.flavor: Captain of the U.S.S. Bozeman, Morgan Bateson was stuck in a temporal loop for nearly 80 years.

crew.name: Locutus of Borg
crew.flavor: Captured by the Borg, Locutus was the name given to an assimilated Jean-Luc Picard.

crew.name: Cyrus Redblock
crew.flavor: A holographic gangster, this Dixon Hill villain held Starfleet participants hostage during a Holodeck malfunction.

crew.name: Tribble Kirk
crew.flavor: Kirk realizes the magnitude of the tribble problem, and orders all tribbles removed from the Enterprise.

crew.name: Tribble Sulu
crew.flavor: A large number of cute tribbles give peace and rest to Sulu.

crew.name: Maquis Tuvok
crew.flavor: On a mission from Starfleet to infiltrate the Maquis, Tuvok joined Chakotay's ship and cell.

crew.name: Riley Frazier
crew.flavor: Once science officer of the U.S.S. Roosevelt, Riley was assimilated during the Battle of Wolf 359.

crew.name: Tribble Chekov
crew.flavor: Chekov accompanies Uhura to the bar aboard Deep Space K-7, where they see a tribble for the very first time.

action.name: I Am Not Afraid, Just Very Tired

crew.name: Miral Torres
crew.flavor: Miral appeared on the Barge of the Dead to her daughter, B'Elanna, during a near-death vision.

crew.name: Platonian Spock
crew.flavor: Spock is made a telekinetic plaything after failing to appeal to the Platonians’ sense of logic.

action.name: Take care, young ladies, and value your wine...

crew.name: Spock and I-Chaya
crew.flavor: Spock is reunited with his childhood sehlat companion when investigating his own disappearance from history.

crew.name: Changeling Bashir
crew.flavor: A Changeling infiltrator replaced Bashir and attempted to destroy the Bajoran sun.

crew.name: Maquis Ro Laren
crew.flavor: Sent to infiltrate a Maquis cell, Ro Laren instead joined the fight against the Cardassians.

crew.name: Breen Disguise Dukat
crew.flavor: Breen Disguise Dukat

crew.name: Enabran Tain
crew.flavor: Former head of the Obsidian Order, Enabran Tain organized a sneak attack against the Founder homeworld.

crew.name: Dr. Hippocrates Noah
crew.flavor: After a transporter accident, Sisko's image is used by a holosuite program to display supervillain Hippocrates Noah.

crew.name: Straal
crew.flavor: Exomycologist and researcher aboard the USS Glenn. Discovered the mycelial network with Paul Stamets.

action.name: Right now, we have to finish getting ready.

crew.name: Ambassador Spock
crew.flavor: Ambassador Spock abuptly vanished, but appeared on Romulus assisting a Romulan-Vulcan reunification movement.

crew.name: Luau Q
crew.flavor: In the Delta Quadrant, Q searches for long lost knowledge - romantic advice from Kim and Paris.

crew.name: Berlinghoff Rasmussen
crew.flavor: A 22nd Century 'inventor', Rasmussen posed as a historian from the future to steal from the Enterprise-D.

crew.name: Captain Kurn
crew.flavor: Kurn, son of Mogh, joined the Officer Exchange Program to meet his long-lost brother, Worf.

crew.name: Laneth
crew.flavor: A subject of a genetic augmentation gone wrong, Laneth struggles to retain her Klingon heart.

crew.name: Iden
crew.flavor: Iden led a rebellion of sentient holograms against their Hirogen creators, who made them to serve as prey for training simulations.

crew.name: Holo-Engineer Zimmerman
crew.flavor: Doctor Lewis Zimmerman arrives on Deep Space Nine to use Bashir as the model for his new Long-term Medical Hologram.

action.name: I'm Here To Make You Immortal
Look Down Every Now And Then

crew.name: Rurigan
crew.flavor: Male Yaderan who lived on Yadera Prime until it was conquered. Then he created a holographic recreation of his lost village.

action.name: And How Do You Plan To Do That?
I Wish You Hadn't Done That

crew.name: Mirror Sisko
crew.flavor: A privateer who served Intendant Kira Nerys in the mirror universe, he later led the Terran Rebellion against the KCA.

action.name: I Am The Very Model Of A Modern Major General

crew.name: Writer Jake Sisko
crew.flavor: During the Dominion occupation of Terok Nor, Jake writes articles for the Federation News Service

crew.name: Lt. JG Sam Lavelle
crew.flavor: A career-oriented and driven officer, Lavelle was highly motivated to take steps to realize what he wants: a promotion.

crew.name: Weyoun Clone 4
crew.flavor: A Vorta clone who oversaw a Jem'Hadar attack ship. Later killed after eradicating a Jem'Hadar rebellion.

crew.name: Racquetball O'Brien
crew.flavor: Chief O'Brien is strongly determined to beat Doctor Bashir at racquetball.

action.name: I Can Play Any Style You Like

crew.name: Blood Oath Jadzia Dax
crew.flavor: Honoring an oath made by Curzon, Jadzia avenged the sons of Kang, Koloth, and Kor.

action.name: There Won't Be A Next Time
The Back Nine at Gedi Prime?

crew.name: Prophet Kira
crew.flavor: Kira would have been willing to surrender herself to the Prophets no matter what the consequences, even if it meant her death.

action.name: I'll Try Not To Disappoint You

crew.name: Commander Sela
crew.flavor: Daughter of Tasha Yar and a Romulan officer, Sela worked to destabilize the Federation.

crew.name: Resistance Burnham
crew.flavor: Commander Burnham is always trying to find a peaceful resolution, but is also ready to think outside the box.

crew.name: Quarren of the Kyrian
crew.flavor: Quarren was able to reexamine everything he knew about Voyager and his discoveries lead to an understanding between the Kyrians and Vaskans.

action.name: Trying to get home, to Mars

crew.name: Lieutenant Sahil
crew.flavor: Officially commissioned as a lieutenant, Sahil’s  dedication to upholding the ideals of the United Federation of Planets is recognized.

action.name: I Would Rather Die Than Leave
All It Takes Are A Few Good Men!

crew.name: Kazon Seska
crew.flavor: After leaving Voyager, Seska later joined the Kazon as consort to First Maje Culluh.

crew.name: Geskana Tucker
crew.flavor: After helping a stranded Ship, Archer and Trip test their mettle in an alien sport.

crew.name: Pel
crew.flavor: Pel disguised herself as a male and displayed great business acumen to fight the notion that females can't earn profit.

crew.name: Chancellor K'mpec
crew.flavor: K'mpec was the Klingon Chancellor, ready for anything to keep peace in the Klingon Empire.

action.name: The Empire Will Not Be Destroyed

crew.name: Flustered Jett Reno
crew.flavor: Muddled with visions of the future, a flustered Jett Reno hurries to deliver the Time Crystal.

action.name: I Don't Respond Well To Threats

crew.name: Carlos Data
crew.flavor: Lieutenant Data takes on the role of Carlos in one of Picard's Dixon Hill holonovels.

crew.name: Heist Bashir
crew.flavor: Bashir doctors the guard's drink with ipecac to allow the heist to be successful.

action.name: And I slip Ipecac into Howard's Drink

crew.name: Skorr Tchar
crew.flavor: The Crown Prince of the Skorr. Determined to return his race to their warrior roots, he’ll do whatever it takes.

action.name: A Noble Death to Win a Great Dream

crew.name: Tawi'Yan Alexander
crew.flavor: Alexander’s change in deployment accelerates Jadzia and Worf’s plans to marry, where he serves as his father’s Tawi’Yan—or sword bearer.

crew.name: Badge-Challenged Linus
crew.flavor: Linus is having more trouble than most crew members learning to use a personal transporter.

crew.name: Returning Saru
crew.flavor: Saru leaves Kaminar and turns down a position as captain to offer Discovery his insight and support.

crew.name: Romulan Kirk
crew.flavor: Kirk masqueraded as a Romulan in order to steal a cloaking device for Starfleet to study.

crew.name: Dahj On The Run
crew.flavor: Her life in danger and her world in shambles, Dahj seeks Picard’s help.

crew.name: Prisoner Spock
crew.flavor: With the help of the Talosians, Spock shows Burnham how and why he escaped from the hospital and that he did not kill anyone.

crew.name: Graduation Amanda Grayson
crew.flavor: As Burnham's adopted mom, she supported her and reminded her to keep her human side.

crew.name: Cellist Adira
crew.flavor: Struggling with the loss and nuances of their joining, Adira practices the Cello as a way of connecting with Gray

crew.name: Acting Captain Tilly
crew.flavor: Tilly’s plan to build a bomb makes for some hard choices as oxygen runs low on Discovery.

crew.name: Union Chakotay
crew.flavor: Costumed as a union officer, Chakotay leads the rescue to save Q and Janeway.

crew.name: Mournful Elnor
crew.flavor: Elnor grieves for Picard, someone who has played such a vital role in his life.

crew.name: Henry Starling
crew.flavor: Henry Starling ushers in the computing revolution by salvaging a wrecked time ship. Now, he looks to travel to the future to take even more.

crew.name: Mirror 'Smiley' O'Brien
crew.flavor: Leader of the Terran Rebellion, 'Smiley' O'Brien commanded the I.S.S. Defiant against the KCA.

crew.name: Zhaban
crew.flavor: A former Tal Shiar agent, Zhaban is now a housekeeper for Picard, and his wisdom may be the greatest thing he can offer the former officer.

crew.name: Fencing Sulu
crew.flavor: Intoxicated by the Psi 2000 polywater, Sulu viewed himself as a musketeer onboard the U.S.S. Enterprise.

crew.name: Vashti Picard
crew.flavor: Before heading to Freecloud to look for Bruce Maddox, Picard visits the Romulan Relocation hub on Vashti to enlist aid.

ships.name: U.S.S. Enterprise NCC-1701-D
ships.flavor: A Galaxy-class vessel famously commanded by Captain Picard. Allows for saucer separation in emergency situations.

ships.name: Galaxy Class Ship
ships.flavor: One of the largest and most powerful classes of ship in Starfleet's history.

ships.name: Borg Cube
ships.flavor: A smaller version of the Collective's ubiquitous and fearsome cubical spacecraft. Features self-repairing systems.

ships.name: Klingon K'Vort Bird-of-Prey
ships.flavor: A versatile craft often used for scouting and patrolling. The K'Vort-class is the most stable iteration of this design.

ships.name: U.S.S. Enterprise NCC-1701
ships.flavor: A Constitution-class vessel made legend under the command of Captain Kirk. A hardy ship that survived many encounters.

ships.name: Constitution Class Ship
ships.flavor: The face of Starfleet in the 23rd century, these heavy cruisers were designed for long-term missions.

ships.name: Cardassian Galor Cruiser
ships.flavor: The "foot soldier" of the Cardassian Union, nimble and destructive. Features multiple phaser arrays.

ships.name: Ferengi D'Kora Marauder
ships.flavor: An enigmatic vessel used for battle and transport. Capable of disabling a deflector shield.

ships.name: Nova Class
ships.flavor: Designed for short-term missions of science and exploration. Features advanced sensor arrays.

ships.name: U.S.S. Defiant
ships.flavor: Initially created for use against the Borg. Equipped with ablative armor and Starfleet's first legal cloaking device.

ships.name: Defiant-Class Ship
ships.flavor: Named after the initial prototype, brought into production during the Dominion War to serve as warships.

ships.name: Jem'Hadar Fighter
ships.flavor: A warship used by the soldier species of the Dominion. Equipped with phased polaron beam weapons

ships.name: Intrepid-Class Ship
ships.flavor: Designed for long-term exploration. Able to land on the surface of a planet and powered by bio-neural gel packs.

ships.name: U.S.S. Voyager
ships.flavor: A Intrepid-class vessel notable for being the first to explore the Delta Quadrant--if not by choice.

ships.name: Romulan D'deridex Warbird
ships.flavor: One of the largest and most advanced vessels in the quadrant. Utilizes a forced quantum singularity as a power source.

ships.name: Constellation Class
ships.flavor: Uniquely designed with four warp nacelles. Most often deployed for exploration and defensive patrols.

ships.name: H.M.S. Bounty
ships.flavor: A Klingon bird-of-prey commandeered by Admiral James T. Kirk. Ironically named Bounty by CMO Leonard "Bones" McCoy.

ships.name: Maquis Raider
ships.flavor: A small and manueverable ship, favored by the Maquis for quick escapes and durability under hostile pursuit.

ships.name: Val Jean
ships.flavor: A Maquis raider commanded by Chakotay. This vessel was destroyed after colliding with the Caretaker's array.

ships.name: I.S.S. Enterprise NCC-1701
ships.flavor: A Constitution-class vessel made legend under the command of Captain Kirk. A hardy ship that survived many encounters.

ships.name: D'Kora Krayton
ships.flavor: An enigmatic vessel used for battle and transport. Capable of disabling a deflector shield.

ships.name: Prakesh
ships.flavor: Gul Dukat's Galor Class vessel, famed for its service in the Klingon-Cardassian War.

ships.name: NX-Class Ship
ships.flavor: The first Starfleet ships to be equipped with warp five engines, allowing exploration beyond neighboring star systems.

ships.name: NX-01 Enterprise
ships.flavor: The flagship of United Earth Starfleet, pivotal in founding the Coalition of Planets, a precursor to the UFP.

ships.name: Hirogen Hunter Ship
ships.flavor: Small but heavily-armed, these vessels are equipped to allow for efficient hunting and processing of game.

ships.name: Hirogen Warship
ships.flavor: Small but heavily-armed, these vessels are equipped to allow for efficient hunting and processing of game.

ships.name: Borg Sphere
ships.flavor: Borg spheres were primarily scout and long-range tactical vessels. Borg cubes sometimes housed Borg spheres as auxillary craft.

ships.name: Borg Sphere 878
ships.flavor: Commandeered by General Kotok and other rebel Borg members of Unimatrix Zero in 2377.

ships.name: Klingon K't'inga Battlecruiser
ships.flavor: A follow up to the powerful D7 Battlecruiser, the K't'inga Class was the primary warship of the Klingon Empire in the late 23rd century.

ships.name: IKS T'Ong
ships.flavor: A K't'inga Class Klingon Battlecruiser, the I.K.S T'Ong gained fame while on a crucial mission under the command of Captain K'Temoc.

ships.name: U.S.S. Shenzhou
ships.flavor: A Walker-class vessel involved in the Battle at the Binary Stars. Ship motto - 'All existing things are really one.'

ships.name: U.S.S. Discovery
ships.flavor: A pioneering science vessel, the crew of U.S.S. Discovery developed a method to safely traverse great distances in an instant with her spore drive.

ships.name: I.S.S. Defiant
ships.flavor: Based on plans taken from the Prime Universe, the I.S.S. Defiant was built and commanded by Mirror 'Smiley' O'Brien to lead the insurgency against Regent Worf.

ships.name: I.S.S. Avenger
ships.flavor: Registered NX-09, the I.S.S Avenger NX-Class Battleship served alongside the I.S.S. Enterprise in the 22nd Century. It met its demise at the hands of the U.S.S Defiant.

ships.name: Terran Empire Constellation Class
ships.flavor: The Constellation Class was a Terran Empire Battle Cruiser that entered service in the late 23rd century.

ships.name: Klingon Sarcophagus
ships.flavor: Flagship of the House of T'Kuvma, the Sarcophagus was armored by thousands of caskets containing remains of Klingon warriors known as the 'Black Fleet'.

ships.name: Andorian Battlecruiser Kumari
ships.flavor: A first of its kind Andorian Battlecruiser named after the first ice-cutter to circumnavigate Andoria.

ships.name: Orion Syndicate Interceptor
ships.flavor: A moderately armed ship used by the Orion Syndicate.

ships.name: Ni'Var
ships.flavor: The Ni'Var was sent by Vulcan High Command to transfer Subcommander T'Pol after her involvement in the destruction of the Vulcan Monastery on P'Jem.

ships.name: Suurok Class Combat Cruiser
ships.flavor: Used as both a Combat Cruiser or a Science Vessel, the Suurok Class was among the fastest and most powerful starships operating in the Vulcan fleet.

ships.name: Miranda Class Ship
ships.flavor: Miranda Class

ships.name: U.S.S Reliant
ships.flavor: U.S.S Reliant

ships.name: Romulan Valdore-type Warbird
ships.flavor: Valdore-type Warbird

ships.name: The Valdore
ships.flavor: A Valdore-type Romulan Warbird, The Valdore battled alongside the U.S.S. Enterprise against the Reman warbird the Scimitar at the battle in the Bassen Rift.

ships.name: Captain Proton Rocket Ship
ships.flavor: The heroic Captain Proton uses this heavily-armed rocket ship to defend Earth against dastardly villains!

ships.name: U.S.S. Enterprise NCC-1701-A
ships.flavor: The second Federation ship to bear the name "Enterprise," this Constitution-class vessel is equipped with improved tactical modifications and boasts a powerful warp core drive.

ships.name: Xindi-Insectoid Patrol Ship
ships.flavor: This small starship used by the Xindi-Insectoids is equipped with multiple directed energy-weapon emitters. As a Patrol ship, it is best known for its speed and maneuverability.

ships.name: The Scimitar
ships.flavor: A heavily-armed warship constructed by Shinzon for the sole purpose of overthrowing the Romulan Empire.

ships.name: U.S.S. Enterprise NCC-1701-E
ships.flavor: A Sovereign-class starship, which, after defeating a Borg Cube, went back in time to prevent the Borg from interfering with humanity's first contact with the Vulcans.

ships.name: Cardassian Keldon Class
ships.flavor: A Cardassian warship used during the 24th century, some of which were secretly enhanced with cloaking under the Obsidian Order and the Romulan Tal Shiar.

ships.name: Assimilated Voyager
ships.flavor: After an attack from a Species 8472 vessel, the Borg Cube defends the Voyager. Janeway agrees to a temporary alliance with the Borg, beginning with the Voyager's assimilation.

ships.name: Federation Fighter
ships.flavor: The cutting edge Federation Fighter first saw major action in the battle against Control at Xahea.

ships.name: The Artifact
ships.flavor: This Borg vessel is severed from the Collective and hosted both research and rehabilitation for xBs. Now active, its queencell, Borg population, and repair systems are engaged.

ships.name: La Sirena
ships.flavor: A Kaplan F17 Speed Freighter for hire, captained by Rios. Supplemented with a variety of Holoprograms to assist across a variety of dangerous emergency situations.

ships.name: Tholian Ship
ships.flavor: Equipped with an energy-dampener and the ability to create the infamous Tholian web, a near impenetrable tractor field.

ships.name: Krenim Weapon Ship
ships.flavor: Developed by Annorax to remove threats to the Krenim Empire via manipulation of the space-time continuum.

ships.name: IKS Negh'Var
ships.flavor: A Klingon warship commanded by General Martok. It spearheaded an attack on Deep Space Nine, an act which dissolved the Federation-Klingon alliance.

ships.name: Generational NX-01 Enterprise
ships.flavor: Finding themselves stranded in the 21st century, the Enterprise crew embarked on a multi-generational journey to prevent their past from yet again becoming the Enterprise's future.

ships.name: Borg Queen's Vessel
ships.flavor: The Borg utilize this vessel to transport the Borg Queen within a shielded chamber that is still capable of immense destruction on the vanguard of assimilation efforts.

ships.name: U.S.S. T'Kumbra
ships.flavor: Commanded by the decorated Captain Solok, this all-Vulcan crewed Nebula-class was at the front lines of the Dominion War.

ships.name: Warship Voyager
ships.flavor: According to the Kyrian Heritage, this warship commanded by the brutal Captain Janeway terrorized the Kyrian people with biogenic weapons.

ships.name: I.S.S. Discovery
ships.flavor: Captained by the fearsome Sylvia "Killy" Tilly, the I.S.S. Discovery was destroyed by Klingon forces upon arrival in the prime universe.

ships.name: U.S.S. Prometheus
ships.flavor: This prototypal Federation ship's experimental assault modes and warp factor 9.99 capability made it a priority target for Romulan hijackers.

ships.name: Harrad-Sar's Barge
ships.flavor: While pretending to command a mining vessel, Harrad-Sar launched an operation to seize control of the Enterprise and deliver it into Orion hands.

ships.name: U.S.S. Excelsior
ships.flavor: The first Starfleet vessel to be fitted with a transwarp drive, the Excelsior was later commanded by Captain Sulu.

ships.name: Xindi-Aquatic Cruiser
ships.flavor: This sleek hydrodynamic starship is the largest and most advanced ship of any of the various Xindi species.

ships.name: NX-02 Columbia
ships.flavor: Commanded by Captain Hernandez, the second NX-Class ship featured a warp five engine with improved hull plating and a changed weapon loadout compared to its predecessor.

ships.name: U.S.S. Glenn
ships.flavor: Sister ship to the U.S.S. Discovery, the crew of the Glenn took greater risks in order to develop their spore drive more quickly, which would eventually prove disastrous.

ships.name: U.S.S. Roddenberry
ships.flavor: This timeless style of ship still finds service in the Federation, providing valuable lessons and experiences to crew members new and old.

ships.name: Malon Export Vessel
ships.flavor: A volatile waste transport ship with a notoriously low life expectancy for its crew.

ships.name: U.S.S. Raven
ships.flavor: This Raven-type exploration vessel carried Magnus and Erin Hansen with their daughter Annika - the first humans to make contact with the Borg.

ships.name: U.S.S. Phoenix
ships.flavor: A Nebula-class vessel commanded by Captain Maxwell who turned vigilante destroying a Cardassian outpost and several ships in Sector 21505.

ships.name: U.S.S. Yeager
ships.flavor: During the Dominion War this light cruiser was often used to protect Deep Space Nine.

ships.name: U.S.S. Hiawatha
ships.flavor: A 23rd century medical frigate that was lost during the Federation-Klingon War.

events.name: Powderkeg
events.description: Just as people are reuniting with family, friends, and crewmates, tempers are reigniting across the galaxy. Q's displacement has inflamed hostilities, old and new. Bridge the divide in the galaxy before all-out warfare erupts.
events.rules:
-- There are two Phases to this Event! Each Phase is individually timed.
-- In this Hybrid Event, you will complete Faction Missions in one phase, and Supply Missions in another phase.
-- Unique Dominion, Maquis, and Section 31 Faction Missions are available during the event. Open the Event to access them.
-- Using any version of Booker, Raffi, D. Troi, Graduation Amanda Grayson or Caregivers will provide a bonus to Faction Missions and Supply Missions.
-- Every Faction or Supply Mission you complete earns you Event Victory Points. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock Threshold Rewards!
-- Community Rewards are also available during Phase 2 only. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock these rewards before the phase change!
-- In this event, Squadrons may also compete to advance up the Squadron leaderboards. Join a Squadron to get more rewards!
